title: Frieze, ca. 1900–40
creditline: Gift of Mark Bitter, Robert Bitter, Ward Bitter, and Tami Bitter Cook
description: Architectural elements to be cut out and applied. The set contains a top cornice molding with beading and acanthus leaves, pilaster capitals and bases, and pilaster shafts. Printed in brown and beige on brown oatmeal paper.
